    "answer_id" : 40891427,
    "question_id" : 17637179,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Go into your Gradle and look for <strong>sourceCompatibility</strong> and change it from <strong>1.6</strong> to <strong>7</strong>. That worked for me at least.</p>\n\n<p>You can also go into your module settings and set the <strong>Source/Target Compatibility</strong> to 1.7.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/4PfX2.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Module settings window</a></p>\n\n<p>That will produce the following code in your Gradle:</p>\n\n<pre><code>compileOptions {\n    sourceCompatibility JavaVersion.VERSION_1_7\n    targetCompatibility JavaVersion.VERSION_1_7\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
